uage=EN>Avalis Schadenfreude</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 36<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/15/02 5:14:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=231.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   The way people speak.</span><hr size=1> Well here is my take on stuff.<br>
<br>
As long I don't see d00dspeak or people using things along the lines of &quot;u r a druid sow me plz&quot; I'm fine.<br>
<br>
As long as I don't get people coming up to me saying &quot;Dude gimme some loot and plat&quot;  I'm fine.<br>
<br>
Hey, I will use shortforms when I'm typing in ICQ and stuff, but in EQ, I will try to play along with whatever I see.  I do use acronyms, say dd, aoe, sow*, etc in regular conversation.  I just USUALLY skip the obviously current colloquial typing styles ingame, like wen ppl talk 2 u like dis lol.  I can't help use them occassionally, I forget u know.<br>
<br>
I enjoy roleplay, but in the middle of a fight, no one wants to see <br>
<br>
&quot;Ah, Lord Avalis ye are powerful an mighty and your spells of mass destruction wound many of our foes most grevious, but consider ye that the foes would be best keep at bay with Adar's mesmerizing enchantments&quot;  <br>
<br>
instead of <br>
<br>
&quot;Av, no AOE, Adar mezzing&quot;  <br>
(everyone keeps thinking my Garrison's Mana Shock is an AOE instead of a DD)<br>
<br>
anyhow, that's all I guess.<br>
<br>
Avalis of Qeynos,<br>
League of Shadows.<br>
<br>
*Being in an highly evil guild, sow is a rare sight to see. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=aradil>Aradil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/15/02 7:42:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=231.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The way people speak.</span><hr size=1> I agree completely. Fighting should be hectic, and orders should be barked out, status checks given rapidly, etc. Think of the last military movie you saw where combat radio communication was shown. Slang and codewords are used all the time (&quot;charlie&quot;, &quot;bogey&quot;, &quot;six o'clock&quot; as a direction, etc). Same applies here, in my opinion. <br>
<br>
Outside of fighting, I type out everything (but I'm lucky, my character gets to the point IC anyway <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ), because that helps ME stay in character. I would like everyone else to do similarly (as in, /laugh or &quot;*laugh*&quot;and not &quot;lol&quot;) but I'm not the boss of anyone, and if it got too bad I wouldn't say anything rude, I'd just find a way to leave the current group of people I was with. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubjond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 179<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/15/02 10:14:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=231.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Oh yeah ..</span><hr size=1> .. if you ever even once use &quot;u&quot; or &quot;ur&quot;, even in fighting, you are a d00d.  Acronyms are OK by me, but those other two will brand you as a d00d forever in my mind. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uavalisschadenfreude.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Avalis Schadenfreude</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 37<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/15/02 11:16:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=231.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Oh yeah ..</span><hr size=1> Great, I am forever branded a d00d because I [slipped up]speaking in front of u. Bleh.  How intolerant.<br>
<br>
Avalis, wizard of Qeynos. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uavalisschadenfreude.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Avalis Schadenfreude</A> at: 1/15/02 11:23:43 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/utrunkbody.showPublicProfile?language=EN>trunkbody</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/16/02 1:27:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=231.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Oh yeah ..</span><hr size=1> WTF is d00D and why is there such and affixiation on avoiding these people. Do you realize you have 30 slots of ignore + when you ignore not only do you not see thier says but you also dont see thier emots nor thier tells.<br>
<br>
Ignore was created for this.  I hear of this d00D but havent seen him, but i hear all these paranoid rants about him continuously.  Point d00D in my direction and ill put him on ignore or just ignore him without it.<br>
<br>
