<br>
Put it this way if you try and use your second phrase for AV, no AOE, Squat Mez . By time you got to half the line you would be dead or the people you trying to keep alive would be dead. The whole idea of RP is to put things in your perspective not to enforce others into your perspectice.  If someone RPs with me i RP back else i dont half and half i do.  I hope you realize there is as many different interpretations of RP as there are people who play on this server, so what is RP to one may be d00D speak to you.<br>
<br>
Who is this d00D?<br>
<br>
Da bod iz n da trunc <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubjond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 180<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/16/02 4:56:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=231.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Actually ..</span><hr size=1> .. even if this wasn't the RP server, I'd probably silently subtract about 20 points from your assumed IQ and cultural level for using &quot;u&quot; and &quot;ur&quot;.  Watchout, trailer-park with free internet hookup!<br>
<br>
Consider this an FYI.  Yes, you do look and sound like ignorant trash when talking like that.  If that's what you want, then go for it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=valquisssilverpalm>Valquiss Silverpalm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 163<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/16/02 5:55:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=231.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Actually ..</span><hr size=1> I've always had a simple explanation for all the short forms.  We are all warriors of one sort or another.  We head out to the battlefields, fight things, and kill things.  Battlefields are busy hectic places and normal forms of address go right out the window.  Ever see a Vietnam flick in which the desperate lieutenent calls in an airstrike with:<br>
<br>
&quot;Hail!  I am in dire need of assistance!  My men are beset by the evil hoards of Charliedom and need the relief of sky skimming bomb angels....&quot;<br>
<br>
I often use short forms while grouping and combat is going on regularly.  When relaxed (and I have unlimited time to type) I go back to full words and proper grammar.  You don't need to justify this ooc, because it makes as much sense ic as ooc.<br>
<br>
Just my opinion.<br>
<br>
Valquiss<br>
<br>
P.S.  That does not extend to using &quot;u&quot; for &quot;you&quot; and &quot;r&quot; for &quot;are&quot; etc.  I think that looks idiotic, and I do have a kneejerk reaction against anyone who does it.  That being said, I have the advantage of typing over 60 words a minute, and not everyone does.  I can look past the typing habits for the sake of a good and loyal companion.  God, I can't imagine how difficult it must be to hunt and peck for individual keys on the keyboard while all hell is breaking loose.   <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=valquisssilverpalm>Valquiss Silverpalm</A> at: 1/16/02 12:41:12 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uqixxfv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>QixxFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Thats not my tail</span><br>  Posts: 49<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/16/02 5:59:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=231.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Actually ..</span><hr size=1> Val right as always <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umollycat.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mollycat</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/16/02 12:46:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=231.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Actually ..</span><hr size=1> It just makes you look like an AOL chatroom reject. If you're okay looking like that, feel free to keep using 'ur' and '4 u' and so on.<br>
<br>
I have rejected people outright for groups because they came across like that.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uavalisschadenfreude.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Avalis Schadenfreude</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 38<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/17/02 4:49:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=231.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Actually ..</span><hr size=1> Do as you all will - I am just saying what I do as well.  I match the level of the conversations that I enter with the person that I speak with.<br>
<br>
If someone speaks with me casually with a a few u's and lol's inserted, I won't mind, or I might joke about it, but I don't suddenly put on an air of superiority, and then call the player behind the character trailer trash or consider them to be of low IQ!!<br>
<br>
If someone roleplays with me, I will roleplay with them.<br>
<br>
If I am the one opening conversation, I'll do so in a role play manner, or a neutral manner at worst.<br>
<br>
Avalis. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uvallshadowstrife.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vall Shadowstrife</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 57<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/17/02 5:14:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=231.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Actually ..</span><hr size=1> I can't imagine people don't type like we do! <br>
<br>
And how about those people that don't speak like us? Them and their own languages. Oh! And you know what REALLY gets me angry? People with accents. What the hell is up with that?<br>
<br>
Anyone see my point here? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uavalisschadenfreude.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Avalis Schadenfreude</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 39<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/17/02 5:23:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=231.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The way people speak.</span><hr size=1> OH!  Also I would like to add in that seeing words like<br>
<br>
&quot;You're&quot;  being typed as &quot;your&quot; consistently  annoys me more greatly than seeing it typed as &quot;ur&quot;<br>
<br>
This kind of thing galls me something fierce.  <br>
-<br>
Here's a extreme sample I think I will put into the polls in a bit.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Picture someone standing over a TPW (total party wipeout if you insist) and saying:<br>
<br>
&quot;Hear lays the bodys of worriors who faught fearcely! May they rest in peice.&quot;<br>
<br>
Now if I saw the idea of &quot;Here lay the bodies of warriors who fought fiercely! (etc)&quot; typed as<br>
<br>
&quot;Woot, would u look at all the bodies, they sure held out a long time before falling.&quot;<br>
<br>
I would much, much, much! prefer the latter.<br>
<br>
A. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uvallshadowstrife.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vall Shadowstrife</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 58<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/17/02 5:33:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=231.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The way people speak.</span><hr size=1> Have you ever tried speaking a foreign language? It's certainly not easy, trust me. <br>
<br>
Most of the people who misspell things like that have English as a second, third, or more language. I speak some Italian, and I have the feeling that if I tried to type out that &quot;Here lay the bodies of warriors who fought fiercely!&quot; in Italian, it would probably sound something like &quot;Lay here bodies of warriors who fought fierce.&quot;, except with more typos. <br>
<br>
Languages are tough, and EverQuest is an international game. You can't expect someone who has studied English for maybe three to four years to be able to speak it as well as someone who has spoken it all their life.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukelisk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kelisk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>No, YOU'RE evil</span><br>  Posts: 87<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/17/02 7:04:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=231.topic&index=13>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The way people speak.</span><hr size=1> I do remember using the &quot;u&quot; and its little shorthand universe in my first days of the internet, on--Guess where? AOL chat.  However, that was different.  That was a chat where people would go to just hang out..  And this is a roleplaying game.  Keyword, roleplaying.  If a warrior runs up to me and says &quot;hay r u in a group yet i kud rly use a hunting parnter&quot;, I really hope their warrior actually phonetically says, &quot;Hay err oo in a group yet i could errlly use a hunting parnter&quot;.  Usually I'll ignore those kind of morons.  However, what really peeves me is the kind of thing mentioned above, where someone says &quot;Your coming soon right, there waiting&quot;, they just come across in my head as ignoramuses (or is that ignoramusi?).<br>
<br>
However, I have discovered something fun as hell to do.  When someone comes up to me and says, &quot;This is my 1st time playing the game can I get some tips&quot; or something to that extent, my response will be...<br>
&quot;What game?  Are you some kind of lunatic?  Remove yourself from my sight.&quot;  As they walk off, not knowing how to use the run button, I'll send them a tell--&quot;OOC: Welcome to the roleplay server.&quot; <p><img src="http://members.hometown.aol.com/bseh14/images/kel.gif"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umollycat.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mollycat</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 35<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/17/02 7:10:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=231.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The way people speak.</span><hr size=1> Spelling mistakes and grammar mistakes are one thing, and nothing serious.<br>
<br>
Abbreviations for common things like SoW are fine too.<br>
<br>
Relics from IRC and AOL chatrooms like '4' for 'for' and 'u' for 'you' are not. Instantly you are labelling yourself as someone who's either spent enough tine with dewds to consider their annoying manner of speech as the norm, or you ARE one.<br>
<br>
People who type like that sound like 12 year old wanna be haxors and thats a sort of person I don't waste much time on.<br>
